register.description: CMU Configuration Register

bitfield.description: Number of parallel CMO threads that can be simultaneously processed.
Number of Queue Entries Configured
Disable pipelining of requests.
Force sequential operation by disabling any parallelism between RangeSets.
Enable Interrupt on Set Completion. 0b0 = Don't interrupt. 0b1 = Interrupt on Completion.

This enables Non-Safe programs to write this register. Out of reset - this bit is 0 which will prevent Non-Safe programs from writing it. Reading is always allowed. This bit can be set to 0x1 only through a Special Safe Monitor API. For more information about the API, see the Initialization chapter. The ROM Code will set this bit to 1 at boot time. The API can be used at runtime by the NS SW to enable/disable when necessary.
Size of smallest cache line size, log2 - 2.

bitenum.description: Line Step = 4 bytes.
Line Step = 8 bytes.
Line Step = 16 bytes.
Line Step = 32 bytes.
Line Step = 64 bytes.
Line Step = 128 bytes.
Line Step = 256 bytes.
Line Step = 512 bytes.

register.description: CMU Status.

bitfield.description: Indicates that at least one set is active.0b0 = CMU is idle. 0b1 = At least one set is active.

register.description: Interrupt Acknowledgment Register. Returns the index of the RangeSet that caused the interrupt. An error bit indicates an error completion.Since there is a queue of interrupt acknowledgments, there is also a valid bit that indicates that there were no more interrupts on the queue.

bitfield.description: Indicates that the label field is valid. Can read the entire queue of entries by reading until get Valid = 0.
Indicates that the RangeSet operation completed with an error.
The index of the RangeSet that caused the interrupt.

register.description: Returns the index of a RangeSet in the Free state.

bitfield.description: Returns 0b0 if Index is valid or 0b1 if no RangeSets available for allocation
Returns the Index of a RangeSet if one is available or zero.

register.description: An index stored to this register frees the RangeSet with that index.

bitfield.description: RangeSet Index written here is deallocated (set to the Free state).

register.description: Debug register to configure how MSuspend from the various CPUs need to be looked at by CMU to either send or not send traffic during debug session.

bitfield.description: This bit can be set so that only if all the MSuspends of all the CPUs present are enabled, CMU will suspend activity to ACP.Bits 3 and 2 need to be set to 0.
This bit can be set so that if any of the MSuspends of CPUs present are enabled, then CMU will suspend activity to ACP.Bits 4 and 2 need to be 0.
This bit enables CMU to look at the MSuspend of a specific CPU to suspend CMU activity to ACP.Bits 4, 3 need to be 0 when bit 2 is 1.

This field allows CMU to look at the MSuspend of a specific CPU to suspend traffic to ACP.When bit 4:2 = 3'b001, bits 1:0 indicates which CPU's MSuspend needs to be looked at. If the appropriate CPU's MSuspend is 1, then CMU will not generate any more activity to ACP and rest of system to have a non-intrusive debug session.When Bit 2 = 0, specific CPU's MSuspend cannot be used to control CMU's activity.

register.description: Controls the operation of one RangeSet of the CMU. Storing this register enqueues or activates the RangeSet.Note: must not write to any of the rangeset registers if State != 0b00. That indicates that previous values have not yet been transferred to the queue!

bitfield.description: Not Safe. Set to NS used to access StartPA register. Writing one to this bit will perform the operation as non-safe. The software can not clear this bit to 0x0 after.

bitenum.description: No notification of normal or error completion.
Interrupt on normal or error completion.

bitfield.description: Wait to start.0b1 = Wait until all previous requests are complete. 0b0 = may proceed in parallel with previous requests.
